Explanation:

We use an array `count` to store the count of each digit from 0 to 9. Iterate through the string `num` once to update the count in `count` array. Then, iterate through the string again to check if the count of each digit matches the length of the string minus the current index. If any digit doesn't match, return false; otherwise, return true. This solution has a time complexity of O(n) and space complexity of O(n), where n is the length of the string.

